“As time continues to wane on in regard to the pandemic,

I've come to realise that it wasn't just these 18 months in

which I spent my time hiding in my bedroom.

I starkly realized that in fact I have spent much of my life running and hiding from the monsters around me, be it viral or otherwise. Coming back to campus is so extremely important to me now, not only because I crave normalcy and to enjoy my youth, but because it is an opportunity for rebirth.”
